      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MY WEE LASS (1) has a fair record and proved too strong last time to win by 2.25 lengths at The Gardens in a handy 22.81 beating No Spark Left. Safe beginner who draws ideally on the inside. Has hit winning form and can go on with it. SIMPLY JUAN (2) has been settling off the speed lately, finishing fourth (22.68) last time in a Grade 5 at this track. Can figure in the finish. MY SOMETHING (8) generally breaks well and with clear running can clear the draw. Latest effort finished 4th in a Grade 5 on April 11 over 400m at The Gardens behind Tiger Tails beaten 5.5 lengths (23.34). Looks a key player on best form. US AND THEM (7) cannot be ruled out.",
